Basics of Kubernetes:
-  It's an orchestration tool (Orchestrator of containers)
- Docker (creates container), Kubernetes (manage container)
-  It has pods (which has containers inside - similar to Docker) & Kubernetes runs these pods
-  Pod (smallest unit in Kubernetes)
- kubectl (command line tool for running kubernetes)

Using: KodeKloud : https://kodekloud.com/studio/labs/kubernetes

HANDS-ON:
1. Check cluster connection
   - kubectl get nodes

2. Create a pod (Ex: nginx)
  - kubectl run nginx --image=nginx

3. Verify if pod is running
   - kubectl get pods

4. Describe pods/ Get detailed info
   - kubectl describe pod nginx

5. Check logs
  - kubectl logs nginx

6. Delete pod
  - kubectl delete pod nginx

7. To run commands inside pods
  - kubectl exec -it nginx -- /bin/bash



